                <h1>Discover the Legacy of Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade</h1>
                <p>The Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade began in 1924, aimed at celebrating the holiday with a festive atmosphere. Originally featuring live animals from the Central Park Zoo, it transformed into a vibrant spectacle of large balloons, floats, and performances. Today, it attracts millions of spectators, both in person and on television, marking the official start to the holiday season.</p>
